gomodel:SYNGO_2916  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"PICK1 colocalizes with clathrin in neuronal dendrites\"\n- \"GFP-PICK1 and dsRed-clathrin showed a colocalizing clustered distribution in dendrites (Fig. 1 A), and PICK1-clathrin clusters were closely associated with the postsynaptic density (PSD) marker Homer. However, a subset of PSDs was not associated with PICK1-clathrin clusters, consistent with previous studies of the distribution of EZs (Blanpied et al., 2002; also see Fig. S2 B). \". Experimental description: - \"Rat embryonic neuronal cultures were prepared from E18 Wistar rats using standard procedures\"\n- Species of over-expressed PICK1 is not stated in the publication. The authors were contacted for additional information (dd 10/4/2018, jon.hanley@bristol.ac.uk). Answer:\n\"Hi,\nIt's rat.\nAll the best\njon\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2916" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

